msgid "IDS_RANKED_REWARDS_TOOLTIP_DESC"
msgstr "<p>If you fail to complete qualification before the sprint ends, you will revert to the starting rank of the league and can earn all rewards again.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If you demonstrate unsportsmanlike conduct during battle, the victory will not count towards reward progress.</p>"

msgid "IDS_SHIP_FEATURES_EARLY_ACCESS_SHIP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>You can obtain the ship before it becomes available for other players to research and purchase.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If you reassign the Commander to this ship, they will be sent to the Reserve after the end of Early Access.</p>"

msgid "IDS_SIGNALS_TOOLTIP_INFO_TEXT"
msgstr "<p>Installed signals are not consumed in Clan and Training battles.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If an installed signal runs out, it will automatically be replaced with a signal of a lower rarity.</p>"

msgid "IDS_SKILL_DESC_DETECTION_DIRECTION"
msgstr "<p>After this skill is mastered, the player will have the direction to the nearest enemy ship indicated to them. </p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The enemy player will be alerted that a bearing was taken on their ship.</p>"

msgid "IDS_SKILL_TRIGGER_ATBAHEAT"
msgstr "<p>Gradually increases secondary gun accuracy at the priority target when continuously firing at any target. Accuracy decreases if the guns aren't used for 15 s or the priority target is changed.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>When the priority target is changed, 80% of accumulated accuracy is preserved.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To set a priority target for secondary armament, press [CMD_FREE_CURSOR], hover the cursor over an enemy ship and press [CMD_SHOOT].</p>"

msgid "IDS_SKILL_TRIGGER_ATBAHEAT_OVERRIDE_FOR_WEB"
msgstr "<p>Gradually increases secondary gun accuracy against the priority target when continuously firing at any target. Accuracy decreases if the guns aren't used for 15 s or the priority target is changed.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>When the priority target is changed, 80% of accumulated accuracy is preserved.</p>"

msgid "IDS_SKILL_TRIGGER_ENEMIESNOTLESSTHANALLIESWITHINGMTRIGGER"
msgstr "<p>Improves your ship's characteristics while the number of allies within your ship's main battery firing range doesn't exceed the number of visible enemy ships.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Your ship is not counted as an allied ship.</p>"

msgid "IDS_STRATEGIC_ACTIONS_CONDITION_REF_SQUAD_CAPTURE_RIBBONS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>While playing together in a Division, the Recruiter and Shipmates must earn a combined total of at least four \"Captured\" or \"Assisted in capture\" ribbons.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Must be completed in a single battle.</p>"

msgid "IDS_STRATEGIC_ACTIONS_CONDITION_REF_SQUAD_DIFFERENT_RIBBONS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>When playing together in a Division, the Recruiter and Shipmates must earn a combined total of 12 or more different ribbons.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>In doing so, each Recruiter and Shipmate must earn at least four different ribbons.</p>"

msgid "IDS_STRATEGIC_ACTIONS_CONDITION_REF_SQUAD_TOP3_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>While playing together in a Division, each Recruiter and Shipmate must survive the battle and finish among the top 3 XP earners on the team.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Complete it in a single battle.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TALENT_PGW103_RIBBONS_1_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Activates upon the spotting of every three enemy ships. </p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The talent's action time measured in seconds is equal to the ship's tier.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ACOUSTIC_TORPEDOES_HOMING_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>The submarine's torpedoes home in on the highlighted sector, taking the speed and course of the ship into account.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>They are most destructive when hitting the side of a ship.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Turn your ship's bow toward incoming torpedoes to reduce the risk of being hit.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCARRIER_AUTOMATIC_CONSUMABLES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>The Damage Control Party consumable is used automatically when either fire or flooding happens, or when a module is incapacitated.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The Fighter is launched automatically, performs reconnaissance duties and repels air attacks when your aircraft carrier is detected by the enemy.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCRAFT_CARRIER_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Aircraft carriers do not have main gun batteries. Their role in battle is to deliver air strikes against enemy forces and perform reconnaissance missions.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>For the best results, try to keep close to the combat action zone, whilst remaining undetected by the enemy.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Aircraft carriers are vulnerable and should be covered at all times by allies.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCRAFT_SQUADRON_CONTROL_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Use the [CMD_THROTTLE_UP] and [CMD_THROTTLE_DOWN] keys to control the speed of your aircraft. Squadron acceleration and deceleration cause engine overheating. When aircraft are flying at cruising speed, their engines cool.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use the [CMD_TURN_LEFT] and [CMD_TURN_RIGHT] keys to change the direction of the aircraft.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCRAFT_SQUADRON_JATO_DETACHABLE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Provides a substantial increase in a squadron's speed during takeoff.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To disable the boosters, press [CMD_THROTTLE_DOWN].</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCRAFT_SQUADRON_MINE_BOMBERS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>This type of aircraft can deploy minefields on the battlefield.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Mines explode on contact with ships, potentially causing flooding and disabling modules.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Place minefields between islands to trap enemy ships.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRCRAFT_SQUADRON_SKIP_BOMBERS_HE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>This type of aircraft carries HE bombs that can set the target ship on fire.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>HE bombs bounce off the water's surface.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>For the greatest efficiency, approach your target from the sides.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIRSUPPORT_BOMB_HE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>This armament is available by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_4].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Carries out aerial bombardment of the marked area with HE bombs.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Most effective against large armored enemy ships.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIR_DEFENSE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>AA defenses and secondary batteries open fire automatically.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To prevent the tracers from exposing your position within a smoke screen, you can disable the AA and secondary guns using the [CMD_SWITCH_ATBA_AIRDEFENSE] key.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_AIR_DEFENSE_SECTOR_GAIN_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Press [CMD_SET_PRIORITY_SECTOR] and select an AA sector to reinforce, depending on the side from which the enemy aircraft are approaching your ship.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>This will decrease the efficiency of the other sectors.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Reinforcement will cease automatically.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ANTI_SUB_AIRCRAFT_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Armament is available by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_4].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Carries out aerial bombardment of the marked area with depth charges.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Can hit hostile submarines only.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ANTI_SUB_IMPROVE_AIRCRAFT_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Press [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_4] to use the armament.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Drops depth charges in the designated area.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>They damage enemy submarines and destroy torpedoes. They deal minor damage to surface ships and surfaced submarines.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARMAMENT_AP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select AP shells by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_2].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Effective against heavily armored targets.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If the armor is not thick enough, shells will over-penetrate and cause only minor damage.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Shells will ricochet if they impact with armor at too sharp an angle.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARMAMENT_CS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select SAP shells by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_1].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Effective against lightly armored targets.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>In cases of non-penetrations or ricochets, no damage is dealt.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARMAMENT_HE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select HE shells by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_1].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Effective against lightly armored ships.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>These shells have high chances of causing fire or incapacitating modules.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARMSRACE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Buffs randomly appear on the map and are displayed as Key Areas.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Pick up buffs to enhance the combat characteristics of your team's ships and aircraft squadrons.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARM_TORPEDO_ALTERNATIVE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>You can switch between different types of torpedoes directly in battle.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The second type of torpedoes is available by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_4].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Switching torpedo types will require additional time.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_ARTILLERY_BURST_FIRE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>The alternative 'Burst Fire' mode allows you to fire several salvos from the main battery guns in quick succession without reloading, with a short minimum interval.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>A long reload is required after each series of salvos.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Toggle the fire mode using the [CMD_TOGGLE_FIRE_MODE] key.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_BATTLESHIP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Battleships carry the most powerful guns. They are slow and are not easy to maneuver, but this is well compensated for by their thick armor.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Their primary purpose is to destroy enemy ships with main battery fire.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_BINOCULARS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>To take better aim at your target, switch to the Binocular View by pressing [CMD_ART_CAMERA].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use the mouse wheel [KEY_MIDDLEMOUSE] to zoom in and out.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_CRUISERS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Good armor protection and powerful guns. Sufficient maneuverability enables these ships to dodge torpedoes from destroyers and avoid shells from battleships.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The duties expected of cruisers include fighting enemy destroyers and cruisers while providing artillery support and protecting allies with anti-aircraft fire.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_DEEP_TORPEDES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Deepwater torpedoes can be selected by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_3].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>They can only strike deep-draught ships and are ineffective against destroyers, but have low detectability.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_DEPTH_CHARGES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Release depth charges by pressing the [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_G] key.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Can hit hostile submarines only.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_DEPTH_CHARGES_SUB_IMPROVE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Press [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_G] to drop depth charges.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>They damage enemy submarines and destroy torpedoes. They deal minor damage to surface ships and surfaced submarines.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_DESTROYERS_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Destroyers excel at surprise attacks through a deadly mix of speed, maneuverability, stealth, and astounding torpedo damage.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Carry out torpedo attacks on enemy heavy ships and provide cover for allied forces by setting smoke screens.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_FIRE_AND_FLOODING_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Fires and flooding damage your ship until they are extinguished.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use 'Damage Control Party' to quickly extinguish fires and stop flooding.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_HYBRID_TACTICS_RETURN_TO_SHIP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Your ship's marker notifies you of various dangers. The chances are that you will have to act real fast.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To switch from operating a squadron and return to controlling your ship, press [CMD_LAND].</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_MAIN_CALIBER_SHOOTING_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Place the targeting reticle over an enemy ship and wait for the gun indicator to turn green—that's when the guns are ready to fire.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Hold [KEY_LEFTMOUSE] for sequential fire.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Double-click [KEY_LEFTMOUSE_DOUBLE] to fire a full salvo from all turrets.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_MINIMAP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>On the Minimap, your ship is displayed in white. Your allied and enemy ships are green and red, respectively. The same color schemes are applied to bases and capture points.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use the [MAP_SCALE_MINUS] and [MAP_SCALE_PLUS] keys to zoom the Minimap in and out.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_MODULES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Ship modules can be disabled.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use 'Damage Control Party' to instantly repair damaged modules.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_PINGED_SECTOR_ON_SHIP_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Submarines use sonar to highlight sectors of ships for torpedo homing.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Use the Damage Control Party consumable to prevent homing.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_RAGE_MODE_ADJUSTMENT_FIRE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Combat Instructions apply a temporary buff to a ship's armament characteristics.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>You can activate Combat Instructions by pressing [CMD_ACTIVATE_RAGE_MODE] once you have completed the activation condition.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Long pauses reduce your progress toward completing the activation condition.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_REPAIR_CONSUMABLE_01_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Repairs damaged modules, extinguishes fires, and stops flooding.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Don't rush to use 'Damage Control Party' if you are under heavy fire.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_REPAIR_CONSUMABLE_02_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Partially restores the ship's HP by repairing minor damage.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The gray zone on the HP indicator displays the amount of HP that can be restored.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SHIP_MANAGEMENT_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Control the speed at which your ship travels using the [CRUISE_SPEED_UP] and [CRUISE_SPEED_DOWN] keys.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To turn, press [CMD_MOVE_LEFT] and [CMD_MOVE_RIGHT].</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SHIP_MOVEMENT_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Ships respond slowly to commands to speed up or stop.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Plan your actions and movement, and be prepared to turn in advance.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_START_TORPEDOES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Take a lead on your target before launching torpedoes. Lock onto a target, and you'll see a white lead wedge.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>To change the width of the spread, press [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_3] again.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Before you launch torpedoes, make sure your teammates are not in their path.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Submarines are effective against cruisers and destroyers.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Their diving depth affects their detectability, viewing range, and interaction possibilities with other submarines and ships.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_ACOUSTIC_TORPEDO_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select torpedo armament by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_2].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Acoustic homing torpedoes home in on a highlighted sector on an enemy ship's hull. Effective against lightly armored targets.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_ANTI_SUBMARINE_WARFARE_DESCRIPTION_IMPROVE_SUBMARINE"
msgstr "<p>Enemy ships are equipped with anti-submarine weapons—depth charges.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Submarines take reduced damage from depth charges while surfaced or at maximum depth.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_ENERGY_BURNING_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>When detected, the submarine's dive capacity depletion rate increases.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If dive capacity is fully depleted, the submarine will ascend automatically.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_ENERGY_IF_SPOTTED_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Dive capacity depletes faster when a submarine has been detected by the enemy.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Try to remain undetected to preserve as much dive capacity as possible until the end of battle.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_ENERGY_MANAGEMENT_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Required to stay underwater and maneuver at depth.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If dive capacity is depleted, the submarine will ascend.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Dive capacity restores on the surface.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_IMPULSE_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select sonar by pressing the [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_1] key.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Sonar pings highlight sectors of enemy ships for torpedo homing.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The highlighted sector has a limited duration.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_SUBMARINE_TORPEDOES_MANEUVERABILITY_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Enemy ships highlighted black cannot be hit with torpedoes.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Torpedoes need a certain time to ascend.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_TACTICAL_AVIATION_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Can carry out swift attacks on enemy ships owing to their high speed.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>A squadron comprises one flight with a significant preparation time.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>The engine boost mounted on aircraft does not restore when they are airborne.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TIPS_TORPEDOES_DESCRIPTION"
msgstr "<p>Select torpedo armament by pressing [CMD_AMMO_SLOT_3].</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Most effective against large armored enemy ships. Maneuverable ships have high chances of dodging a torpedo attack.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TOOLTIP_BATTERY_MAX_CAPACITY"
msgstr "<p>Required to stay underwater and maneuver at depth</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>If dive capacity is depleted, the submarine starts emergency surfacing</p>"

msgid "IDS_TOOLTIP_GUARANTEED_VISIBILITY_SUBMARINE"
msgstr "<p>Range at which the ship is guaranteed to be detected by an enemy ship, even if within smoke, behind an island, or underwater.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>At maximum depth, a submarine can only be detected by hostile submarines or Hydroacoustic Search.</p>"

msgid "IDS_TOOLTIP_WAVE_DURATION_SECOND_HIT"
msgstr "<p>Hitting a target with a sonar ping highlights a sector that torpedoes will home in on.</p><p class=\"p_spacing\"> </p><p>Hitting a highlighted sector a second time extends the duration of the effect and improves the maneuverability of homing torpedoes.</p>"
